    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 2003 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2), featuring the refined 3.6-liter M96 flat-six engine utilizing VarioCam Plus for optimized valve timing and lift. This power plant is mated to a G96 6-speed manual transaxle, delivering power through a traditional rear-engine, rear-wheel-drive layout. The mechanical integrity is bolstered by a documented IMS bearing retrofit and a recently replaced rear main seal (RMS). The chassis retains its precision with a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry, while braking is handled by four-piston monoblock calipers over cross-drilled rotors. The induction system and throttle mapping remain crisp, providing linear power delivery across the rev range. While the exterior shows minor age-appropriate patina, the internal mechanical synchronization and hydraulic steering feedback offer a pure, analog driving experience typical of this era of Zuffenhausen engineering.",
